('388-390 Greenwich St., New York, NY 10013, U.S.', 'Samuel Osgood', 'An American multinational investment bank and financial services corporation headquartered in New York City. The company was formed by the merger of banking giant Citicorp and financial conglomerate Travelers Group in 1998; Travelers was subsequently spun off from the company in 2002. Citigroup owns Citicorp, the holding company for Citibank, as well as several international subsidiaries. Citigroup is incorporated in Delaware.', 'Citigroup', 'Financial Services', 1, 1000000, 1),
('8 Canada Square, London, England, UK', 'Sir Thomas Sutherland', 'HSBC Holdings plc is a British multinational investment bank and financial services holding company. It is the second largest bank in Europe, with total assets of US$2.984 trillion (as of December 2020). HSBC traces its origin to a hong in British Hong Kong and its present form was established in London by the Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation to act as a new group holding company in 1991; its name derives from that companys initials.', 'Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation', 'Financial Services', 2, 1000000, 2),
('Paradeplatz, Zürich, Switzerland', 'Thomas Gottstein', 'Credit Suisse Group AG is a global investment bank and financial services firm founded and based in Switzerland. Headquartered in Zürich, it maintains offices in all major financial centers around the world and is one of the nine global "Bulge Bracket" banks providing services in investment banking, private banking, asset management, and shared services. It is known for strict bank–client confidentiality and banking secrecy. The Financial Stability Board considers it to be a systemically important bank.', 'Credit Suisse', 'Financial Services', 3, 1000000, 3),
('Edinburgh, Scotland, UK', 'Alison Rose', 'The Royal Bank of Scotland (Scottish Gaelic: Banca Rìoghail na h-Alba, commonly abbreviated as RBS) is a major retail and commercial bank in Scotland. It is one of the retail banking subsidiaries of NatWest Group, together with NatWest (in England and Wales) and Ulster Bank. The Royal Bank of Scotland has around 700 branches, mainly in Scotland, though there are branches in many larger towns and cities throughout England and Wales.', 'Royal Bank of Scotland', 'Financial Services', 4, 1000000, 4),
('Montrouge, France', 'Philippe Brassac', 'Crédit Agricole Group (French: [kʁedi aɡʁikɔl]), sometimes called "la banque verte" (English: "The green bank") due to its historical ties to farming, is the world''s largest cooperative financial institution. It consists of a network of Crédit Agricole local banks, the 39 Crédit Agricole regional banks, and a central institute, the Crédit Agricole S.A.', 'Calyon', 'Financial services', 5, 1000000, 5),
('225 Franklin Street, Boston, MA, U.S.', 'Nick Ring', 'Columbia Threadneedle was formed in 30 March 2015 as the result of a merger between Columbia Management Group (an investment advisor and sponsor of mutual funds) and Threadneedle Asset Management (a non-US focused asset management firm based in the United Kingdom). Columbia Management Group and Threadneedle Asset Management were subsidiaries of Ameriprise Financial which were acquired in 2010 and 2003 respectively.In April 2021, Columbia Threadneedle acquired BMO''s European asset management business for $845 million', 'Threadneedle', 'Investment management', 6, 1000000, 6),
('London, England, UK', 'Amanda Blanc', 'Aviva plc is a British multinational insurance company headquartered in London, England. It has about 33 million customers across 16 countries. In the United Kingdom, Aviva is the largest general insurer and a leading life and pensions provider.Aviva also has a focus on the markets in Europe and in Asia and, in particular, on the growth markets of China and South East Asia. Aviva is also the second largest general insurer in Canada. ', 'Aviva', 'Financial services', 7, 1000000, 7),
